description:
For each of us, the word "president" is likely to conjure up various images. The Seventh-day Adventist church has one of its own. Pastor Ted Wilson is the president of the General Conference of Seventh-day Adventists, a position he has held since 2010. An ordinary man with exceptional leadership abilities and a strong desire to serve on the side.

He is a man who understands how to connect with people from various cultures and has inspired a desire to serve people worldwide.

Learn more about this incredible man, the modern-day Moses of God's people. Watch the video to gain insight into his life and ministry.
